      "writtenOn": "2020-12-01T20:23:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This pattern scares me. Having thousands of helper functions in a header seems like a recipe for painful build times and it\u0027s not clear that the linker will reliably strip them out. I don\u0027t think it\u0027s a good idea to have an exhaustive swizzle list just because we can; if we insist on it, I\u0027d suggest converting these to a lighter-weight representation that won\u0027t force the compiler to generate and discard so much chaff. (Prototypes in header, impl in cpp? Get the preprocessor involved somehow?).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 114,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 123,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "c31bce6e553004c1ae30060bfd36d32b2ede2d91",
